@node "Introduction"

  Because the movieshop user-menu isn“t able to contain a great number of pro-
  grams, scripts and tools I created this program for my movieshop-tools.

  With this program you are able to run all my tools using only one entry in
  your movieshop-menu.


@endnode

@node "Requirements"

  Following soft- and hardware is required to use this program:

  HARDWARE:                                               SOFTWARE:

  - Amiga or DraCo-computer                               - Movieshop version 4.2 or higher
  - AGA-graphics                                          - rexxreqtools.library
. - OS 3.0 or higher
  - VLab-motion or DraCo-motion
  - Graphic-card (optional)


@endnode

@node "Legal stuff"

  This program is FREEWARE !!!
  You are allowed to copy and spread it, but there are the following limitations:

  - Only spread the original-archive.
  - It“s NOT allowed to add or to remove files from/to the archive.
  - The archive can be spreaded by mailboxes, pd-series (fish, etc.), the www and
    the aminet..
  - It“s forbidden to “make money“ with this tool !!!

@endnode

@node "Installation"

  To run this program correctly, note the following instructions:

  1) Copy the “rexxreqtools.library“ in your LIBS: drawer on your systempartition.
  2) Copy the file “MS-TOOLBOX“ in your “MOVIESHOP/MACROS“ drawer.
  3) Create the following directories in your “MACROS“ drawer:

     MOVIESHOP / MACROS
                   |
                   =====> FALCON“s_MS-TOOLS =====> EXE        This drawer contains the executables.
                                              |
                                              ===> HELP       This is for the help-files of my ms-tools.
                                              |
                                              ===> KEYFILES   If you get keyfiles for my programs, store it here.
                                              |
                                              ===> PREFS      This drawer is used from any programs to store the prefs.


     Please check the correkt names of the drawers. In other way the toolbox cannot run correctly.


  4) If you want, you can select a hotkey-entry for the toolbox in your movieshop.


  HINWEIS: With the toolbox you are able to run every executable file, but NOT arexx-scripts or others.
           You can store every program into the “EXE“ drawer. It“s not only for my ms-tools.
           It“s possible to start (for example) games with the toolbox... but do you really want to play ???



@endnode

@node "Usage"

  - Start your movieshop and open a project.
  - Start the ms-toolbox via the user-menu or - is you have created - with the hotkey.
  - A window will be opened which contains all files which are stored in the “EXE“
    drawer.
    There is NO check for text-, arexx- and other fileformats. So make sure, that you
    have installed only executables in this drawer.
  - Double-click on the program you want to start. That“s all...

@endnode

@node "Known bugs"

  - Please make sure, that there is not running any program started by using the
    toolbox.
    There is no known bug and it“s possible to start any programs with the toolbox,
    but the author did not give any guarantees...

@endnode

@node "Unknown bugs"

  If you get any error while running the ms-toolbox, please send me an email.

  Please tell my your system-configuration as exactly as you can.

  - comuter
  - operating-system
  - processor (-board)/coprocessor
  - chipram / fastram
  - graphicboard
  - other things (boards, drives, CD-roms, ans so on)
  - movieshop-version


  What“s the occured error ???

  - When did the error occure (for example: If I click here, this or that happens...)
  - Can you avoid the error by doing something ???


  IMPORTANT NOTE: You use this program AT YOUR OWN RISK !!!
                  I can not give any guarantees !!!

@endnode

